Consider the following C code for stack implementation using arrays:

void push(int stack[], int *top, int maxSize, int value) {
    if(*top == maxSize - 1) {
        printf("Stack Overflow\n");
        return;
    }
    stack[++(*top)] = value;
}

If maxSize = 5 and we call push five times without popping, what happens on the sixth call?
